- The outermost number of ring t is Nmax(t) = 1 + 3t(t+1). Solve Nmax(t-1) < 2026 ≤ Nmax(t) → t = 26, with Nmin(26) = 1952.
- Let s = n − Nmin(t) = 74. Each side has length t, so side k = ⌊s/t⌋ = 2 and position p = s mod t = 22.
- The six neighbors are:
